-- 
South Africa Sugar Production Will Increase in 2012, USDA Says

-- B y   B l a i r   E u t e n e u e r
-- 
2011-09-21T20:00:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/south-africa-sugar-production-will-increase-in-2012-usda-says.html
Sugar production in  South Africa 
will increase to 2 million metric tons in the year that began
April 1 from an estimated 1.985 million a year earlier, when
drought reduced output by 12 percent, the U.S. Department of
Agriculture’s  Foreign Agricultural Service  said in a  report 
posted today on the agency’s website.  Exports will rise to 480,000 tons from an estimated 430,000
tons, while domestic consumption jumps to 1.67 million tons from
an estimated 1.62 million, the agency said in the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blair Euteneuer in Chicago at 
 beuteneuer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net  